subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
FEMALE. Macropterous (
Figs 8A, G
). Fore wing with hyaline cross band behind marginal vein complete and with entirely white setae (
Figs 8G, H
); infuscate region basal of hyaline band with uniformly dark setae and about 2.0–2.5× wider than cross band; basal region with basal cell, mediocubital fold and cubital and vanal areas uniformly setose, though at least basal cell with comparatively inconspicuous white setae (
cf
. 
Fig. 5B
). Head (
Fig. 8C
) with scrobal depression separated from anterior ocellus by distance greater than, but by less than 1.5×, longitudinal diameter of ocellus. Antenna (
Fig. 8I
) with fl2 longer than pedicel but not all funiculars longer than wide, with at least apical two funiculars quadrate to slightly transverse (
Fig. 8I
, insert). Mesosoma, including procoxa (
Fig. 8F
), entirely dark, with concave posterior part of mesoscutum distinctly green or sometimes blue to purple in distinct contrast to rest of mesoscutum (
Fig. 8B
); mesotibial apical spur pale to variably darkly infuscate (
Fig. 9B
); mesotarsus with basal three or four tarsomeres pale, though apical tarsomere dark and penultimate tarsomere often variably distinctly infuscate (
Fig. 9B
). Mesoscutum (
Fig. 8B
) with convex anterior part of medial lobe entirely punctate-reticulate to mesh-like reticulate, with somewhat larger reticulations posteriorly, and with posterior concave part of mesoscutum broadly setose with white setae medially, though apices of setae not extending laterally to carinate margin of lateral lobe; mesoscutal lateral lobe with bare, minutely mesh-like-coriaceous band anterior of posteromedian carina relative to more mesh-like reticulate to reticulate-imbricate sculpture on outer inclined surface (
Figs 8B, D
). Profemur ventrally with distinct, acute, spine-like denticle (tooth) within about apical third (
Fig. 9A
: arrow).

MALE. Antenna (
Fig. 9F
) with scape yellow, pedicel dark dorsally but pale ventrally; flagellum with at least basal one or two flagellomeres paler relative to darker brown apical flagellomeres such that darker multiporous plate sensilla contrasting in colour with surrounding cuticle (
Fig. 9F
), and consisting of clava and seven funiculars, with all funiculars obviously longer than wide and clava subequal in length to combined length of apical two funiculars (
Fig. 9F
). Head (
Fig. 9G
) with frons mesh-like coriaceous to variably distinctly roughened, mesh-like reticulate to reticulate-rugulose. Mesopleurosternum entirely dark or with variably distinctly differentiated, paler, transepisternal and femoral lines forming Y-shaped mark (
Figs 9D
: fml, tsl). Legs (
Fig. 9C
) with pro- and mesotrochanters and trochantelli infuscate to dark, but metatrochanter and trochantellus pale; pro- and mesofemora mostly dark but narrowly pale apically, and metafemur entirely dark; pro- and mesotibiae entirely pale, but metatibia almost entirely dark, only narrowly pale basally for distance at most about equal with apical width of tibia; tarsi pale. Fore wing (
Fig. 9H
) with costal cell dorsally setose along leading margin only apically, for distance less than half length of cell (
Fig. 9I
); basal cell bare or variably extensively setose excluding setae along basal and mediocubital folds (
Fig. 9I
); disc with large, quadrangular speculum, either open posteriorly (
Fig. 9H
) or partly to completely closed posteriorly by line of inconspicuous white setae.

